                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Tax-free tag awaits Deshdrohi
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                               
	Patna, Nov. 14: The Bihar government is contemplating to offer tax-free status to Kamal Rashid Khans film Deshdrohi, which was described as a big hit in the state on its release today.         
	The movie in the two cinemas here booked full house in all the four shows. We are planning to make Deshdrohi tax-free to let more people watch and enjoy it at a relatively less ticket fees, said deputy chief minister Sushil Kumar Modi, adding: But we will take a decision only after chief minister Nitish Kumar and I watch it.        
	A theatre here is about to organise a special show for Nitish and other VIPs to watch it soon, sources in the government said.        
	The cinemas witnessed various spells of thunderous clapping from the audience in course of the show with photographers and reporters of different channels vying among themselves to get peoples reaction on the film.        
	Many of them, who watched Deshdrohi, said that the movie had given the message of unity and brotherhood among people living in different states and speaking different languages.                                                                                                                                                                         
